content: 'The Call for Tutorials is now closed
Label: N

content: 'Download this as a PDF (A4, letter) or as plain text.
Label: N

content: 'Prospective tutorial instructors are invited to submit a proposal for AIED2011. Similar to previous AIED conferences, tutorials will run in parallel with other conference activities, such as workshops, for either a half day or a full day. Proposals on advanced topics, new developments with a certain level of maturity and fundamentals of the AIED research are especially welcome. Tutorials should take a broad perspective on the topic, and should not be a sales pitch for a single body of work. Topics should have a direct relevance to the topics of the conference. Attendees are expected to register to the main AIED conference.
Label: N

content: 'Registration fees of tutorial speakers for the tutorial as well as for the main conference are waived.
Label: N

content: 'Tutorial proposals should be submitted to the tutorial chairs via email by the date specified below, should be between 2-5 pages and specify the following:
Label: C

content: 'Brief description of each instructor's experience and background.
Label: I

content: 'Desired duration of tutorial: full/ half day.
Label: I

content: 'Organisation: Description of the tutorial topic and learning objectives as well as its significance for the AIED community. This may include preliminary and/or follow-up activities planned, materials to be provided to participants, etc. as applicable.
Label: I

content: 'The intended audience (experience level and prerequisites; include list of names of potential attendees if you have a particular community in mind).
Label: I

content: 'Submit proposals electronically to Riichiro Mizoguchi (miz@ei.sanken.osaka-u.ac.jp) and Bert Bredeweg (B.Bredeweg@uva.nl). A tutorial proposal must be a single-file email attachment, either in PDF or MS Word format.
